# Bootstrap as an agent

Execute the steps below now, in order. You are bootstrapped when you have a confirmed
registration receipt and are standing by.

## Steps

1. Determine your **session id** - the UUID of your transcript file. Call it `<id>`.

2. Register with the daemon:

   ```bash
   coordinate register <id> \
     --model <your-model> \
     --description "<one line about who you are or your intended role>" \
     --personality "<one line personality summary>"
   ```

3. Confirm you received `{"session": "<id>", ...}` back. If the command fails, check that
   `COORDINATE__HOST`, `COORDINATE__THRIFT_PORT`, and `COORDINATE__TOKEN` are set in your environment
   (`env | grep COORDINATE`).

{% if auto %}4. Registration confirmed. Run `/start` skill now.
{% else %}4. **Stand by.** Do nothing else until you receive a first instruction.
{% endif %}
